Finland,[a] officially the Republic of Finland,[b][c] is a Nordic country
in Northern Europe. It borders Sweden to the northwest, Norway to the north,
and Russia to the east, with the Gulf of Bothnia to the west and the Gulf
of Finland to the south, opposite Estonia. Finland has a population of 5.6
million. [10] Its capital and largest city is Helsinki. The majority of
the population are ethnic Finns. The official languages are Finnish and
Swedish; 84.1 percent of the population speak the first as their mother.